#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:47
msgid "Research shows that peer review can suffer from implicit bias—just like the hiring processes—that disadvantages women, minorities and people from less-prestigious institutions. There is also research attesting to higher quality in signed reviews compared to anonymous reviews |ref_1|_, |ref_2|_, |ref_3|_. For this reason, we want to educate our reviewers about bias in the review process, and equip them with tools to interrupt this bias."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:49
msgid "Human beings are consistently, routinely, and profoundly biased. We not only are profoundly biased, but we also almost never know we are being biased. (Interested? |ref_4|_, |ref_5|_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:51
msgid "First, by realizing and accepting that we all have bias, we can learn to watch for it in ourselves and help others who work with us to do the same. This process of building awareness is analogous to what happens when we step on the clutch in a manual-transmission automobile. The motor doesn't stop running (bias doesn't stop), but the car is no longer moving forward. When we are on the lookout for our biases, they are less likely to blindly dictate our decisions. |ref_6|_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:53
msgid "Be on the lookout! As you review, ask yourself …"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:55
msgid "Are there things about the proposal that particularly influence my impression? Are they relevant to the talk?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:57
msgid "What assessments have I already made about the speaker? Are these grounded in solid information or are they simply my interpretations?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:59
msgid "Does this person's work remind me in any way about myself? Is my own agenda influencing my assessment of this proposal? Are there past experiences of mine that are influencing factors?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:61
msgid "Does this person remind me of anybody, positively or negatively? (Be careful to observe rater biases relating to current projects or work. It is easy to slip into evaluating proposals more or less positively because they happen to be on a project that is important to you.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:63
msgid "Does this person's academic institution, place of employment, or any other affiliations affect how I perceive their work?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scipy-conference/manual/program/reviewer_guidelines.rst:66
msgid "Things to think about as you prepare to review:"
